Six people were arraigned yesterday before a Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Akure, Ondo State for the armed robbery which occurred at Idoani in Ose Local Government Area a fortnight ago.
The accused are Isaiah Yusuf, Joshua Egumah Abuse, Idris Alli Abdullahi, Philip Adeni, Odeh Friday Francis and Peter Ufomadu. They were arraigned before Chief Magistrate Victoria Bob-Manuel for alleged armed robbery and felony. Four officials of First Bank Plc, an Inspector of Police and two bank customers were killed during the robbery on April 8. Witnesses said the gunmen stormed the area about 2p.m., shooting sporadically as they blew open the bank security door with dynamite.
During the operation which lasted about one hour, seven people including bankers, a police Inspector, and about two ATM customers were shot dead. But yesterday, the police prosecutor, Mr. Ezekiel Olawoye, brought six suspects to the court. Olawoye alleged that the accused conspired to commit felony to wit armed robbery and thereby committed an offence contrary to and punishable under Section 6(a) and (b) of the Robbery and Firearms Act, Cap RII, laws of the Federation of Nigeria 2004.
The charge reads: “That you, Isaiah Yusuf, Joshua Egumah Abuse, Idris Alli Abdullahi, Philip Adeni, Odeh Friday Francis and Peter Ufomadu and others at large, on the same day, date, time and place in the aforementioned magisterial district, did conspire together to commit felony to wit murder contrary to and punishable under Section 324 of the Criminal Code, Cap 37, Vol. 1, laws of Ondo State of Nigeria 2006.
However, the court did not take the plea of the accused. The magistrate ordered that the accused be remanded in prison custody till May 2, pending the advice from the office of the Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP).